  "prompt": "How can I remove the HTC One X System folder, which still appears on my Windows 7 list of devices?",
  "response": "To remove the HTC One X System folder from your Windows 7 device list, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. Device Manager Method:\n- Open Device Manager\n- Locate the HTC One X device\n- Right-click and select \"Uninstall\"\n- Check the box \"Delete the driver software for this device\" if available\n- Restart your computer\n\n2. Windows Explorer Method:\n- Open Windows Explorer\n- Navigate to Computer/This PC\n- Right-click on the HTC One X device\n- Select \"Eject\" or \"Safely Remove\"\n\n3. Control Panel Method:\n- Open Control Panel\n- Go to Hardware and Sound\n- Click on \"Devices and Printers\"\n- Right-click the HTC One X device\n- Select \"Remove device\"\n\n4. Registry Edit (Advanced Users):\n- Open Registry Editor (regedit)\n- Navigate to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Enum\\USB\n- Look for folders related to HTC One X\n- Delete the corresponding registry keys\n- Restart computer (Caution: Only do this if you're comfortable with registry editing)\n\nIf these methods don't work, you might need to restart your computer or reconnect the device.",
